The sixth SA Citizen Satisfaction Index shows citizen's satisfaction and trust in government is at an all time low. JOHANNESBURG - The sixth SA Citizen Satisfaction Index shows citizen's satisfaction and trust in government is at an all-time low. Those who took part cited a lack of municipal service delivery as one of the biggest problems. READ: Poll tracks changing political tides The Founder of the South African Customer Satisfaction Index Adré Schreuder reported Cape Town has the least difference between the expectations of citizens and outcomes but stressed people are still experiencing dissatisfaction. Basic service delivery like water, sanitation, electricity, and waste removal were persistent areas of unhappiness for citizens.